overview: The user initiated a request for thorough browser-based testing of the
  sleep questionnaire application. The agent systematically navigated through
  the application, testing the questionnaire flow, form validation, report
  generation (including PDF download), and admin login functionality. During
  testing, the agent confirmed that most features were working as expected,
  including conditional fields and API endpoint responses. It identified minor
  issues such as ESLint warnings and a generic page title. Following the
  testing, the user requested these issues be fixed. The agent then updated the
  page title and prepared to address the warnings, committing all changes in a
  series of atomic, conventionally-formatted commits, covering schema updates,
  form section enhancements, report analysis improvements, PDF generation, CSV
  export, and metadata updates.
